'''Donaldson Smith's nightjar''' ('''''Caprimulgus donaldsoni''''') is a species of [[nightjar]] in the family [[Caprimulgidae]]. It is found in [[Ethiopia]], [[Kenya]], [[Somalia]], and [[Tanzania]]. It was named in honor of the 19th-century American explorer [[Arthur Donaldson Smith]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Beolens |first1=Bo |last2=Watkins |first2=Michael |last3=Grayson |first3=Michael |title=The Eponym Dictionary of Mammals |date=2009 |publisher=The Johns Hopkins University Press |location=Baltimore |isbn=978-0-8018-9304-9 |page=383 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Jar_DwAAQBAJ |access-date=12 April 2024}}</ref>

